<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8211; A <a href="//e360.yale.edu/feature/how_can_we_make_people_care_about_climate_change/2892/">2015 Yale Environment 360 interview</a>Â with Per Espen Stoknes, a Norwegian psychologist and economist who wrote &#8220;<a href="//www.chelseagreen.com/what-we-think-about-when-we-try-not-to-think-about-global-warming">What We Think About When We Try Not To Think About Global Warming: Toward a New Psychology of Climate Action</a>.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8211; A Guardian article by Greg Harmon from 2014: &#8220;<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2014/nov/10/brain-climate-change-science-psychology-environment-elections">Your brain on climate change: why the threat produces apathy, not action</a>.&#8221;</p>
